GitHub.
	- GitHub is the Open Source Repository Maintained By Google.

GitHub Opearations.

1. Creating the Repository Locally.

2. Assign the User Credentials to the Repository.

3. Create the Files to the Repository

4. Commit the Changes to the Repository

5. Creating the Branch

6. Merge the Branches

7. Integration Of GitHub to the IDE (Ecilipse, Visual Studio, WebStrom)

8. Commit the Changes to The Cloud Repoistory.

9. Push Code to the Cloud Repoistory

10. Pull the Code From the Cloud Repository.

11. Code Comparision

12. Merge Conflicts Resolve.


Create the Repository Locally.
-

Step 1.
	Download and Install the GIT.

	Website : https://git-scm.com/download/win
	file name : Git-2.13.2-64-bit.exe


Step 2.
	Create the Directory (folder)

	Ex.
		E:\demo

Step 3.
	Execute the Following Command on GitBash
> git init

[Note . Automatically demo folder converted as local repoistory]

2. Add the User Details (Credentials) to the Repository.
	- we can add "name" & "email" to to the Repository in order to track the changes

> git config --global user.name "NareshIT"

> git config --global user.email "hr@gmail.com"


3. Create the Files to The Repository.

> touch sample.js

4. Commit the Files to the Repository
 
> git status
	[ red color files indicating untracked files]

> git add sample.js

> git commit

> press the "I" in keypad

> type "initial commit"

> press "ESC"

> type ":wq"

> press enter

> git status

From 2nd Commit Onwards.

> git add sample.js
> git commit -m "Class Created !"

> git log (Displays the Log Console)


5. Creating the Branch
> git branch team_one


6. Checkout the Branch
> git checkout team_one


7. Merge the Files

> git merge team_one


Installation Of Softwares with GitHub Integration.

1. Download and Install the GIT.

	WebSite : https://git-scm.com/download/win
	File Name : Git-2.13.2-64-bit.exe


2. Download and Install the NodeJS

	Website : https://nodejs.org/en/download/
	File Name : node-v6.11.0-x64.msi


3. Create the Account with the GitHub
	Website : https://github.com/join


4. Download and Install WebStrom IDE.
	
	Website : https://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm/download/ download-thanks.html?platform=windows

	file name : WebStrom-2017.1.4.exe



5. Checkout the Code from GitHub.

	URL : https://github.com/ajsnaresh/AJS_Classes.git


6. Download and Install the MongoDB.

	Website : https://www.mongodb.com/dr/fastdl.mongodb.org/win32/mongodb-win32-x86_64-2008plus-ssl-3.4.5-signed.msi/download

	file name : mongodb-win32-x86_64-2008plus-ssl-3.4.5-signed.msi


7. Install the Automation Tools

bower
-
> npm install -g bower

gulp
-
> npm install -g gulp


8. Download and Install the RestClient (PostMan)

	Website : https://app.getpostman.com/app/download/win64

	file name : Postman-win64-5.0.2-Setup.exe


































